values:
I doubt anyone still reads this.

I think I used to be a happier person. Anymore I feel unfulfilled and far from content. I'm always in a mood or a funk or I'm just down and I hate it. This is not me. This is not the girl who doesn't wear white underwear because life is too short. This is mundane.

This summer had so much potential. It was the interim, the end of high school and the beginning of a new life and the last couple months that we would all be together as the same people we are. Come next summer, come Christmas even we'll all be irrevocably changed, for better and for worse, but for good. We might have the same bond but we won't be the same people, not exactly. Which is good, it's exciting and intriguing and so tempting, but it's terrifying and huge at the same time. We're together for the last time, but it's sort of dwindled into routine. 

I am a firm believer in the whole people-were-meant-to-be-in-pairs thing. I don't function well alone. I've got the whole unrequited love thing down pat, but it is tearing me up inside. I can't stand the whole internal "will I or won't I" conflict. I won't. I know I won't. I can't handle rejection to the extreme that I can't put myself in the position of even the possibility of rejection. I can't handle saying goodbye without knowing we'll say hello again.

I'm terrified of arguments. I've never been in a real fight with anyone that ended up alright. It always ends in walking the other way in the hallway and avoiding certain places that categorically define our relationship. If I tell you I'm in love with you it won't end well.

But I realize I'm being a little melodramatic. In general, life is good. I'm happy. I'd be happier if my car hadn't died on me last week, but overall things could be worse. I have the end of summer, I have the next four years and after that, my entire future is layed out like a blank canvas in front of me. I have all of you. I love all of you from the deepest part of my heart. Probably no one will actually read this, but it doesn't matter. You know how much you mean to me. You're my life and my well-being. You're my peace of mind. You're my sunshine and my cloudy day.

I am so blessed to have these past 18 years. 

I love you.

I watched Eternal Sunshine earlier and (as always) found exactly what I needed.

Clementine: This is it, Joel. It's going to be gone soon. 
Joel: I know. 
Clementine: What do we do? 
Joel: Enjoy it. 

I will.
Hello Again makes my heart hurt.

"It seems only yesterday I used to believe
there was nothing under my skin but light.
If you cut me, I would shine.
But now when I fall upon the sidewalks of life,
I skin my knees. I bleed."



if i never stopped smiling, 
in a hundred thousand years,
it would be too soon.

if i never finished playing, if i
never grew up, if you never 
stopped growing, if we never quit,
if no one ever stopped moving

laughing

loving

learning

pretending


that would be okay.

i'd smile and go with it and think to 
myself but never tell you. but if i did, 
it
would be alright.

you told me so once at the lake

at the shore

on the porch, you whispered because it was late
and we were so so close to everyone around us

"everything will be alright. watch."

so i watched. i watch.

i'll keep watching, for the next 
one hundred thousand years.
and we both know


it will be too soon.

but we'll never stop

smiling.

for the next ten mintues i'll sit and pretend
i can live in the moment, smile for the here and now and
kiss like anyone else.

i'll pretend it's alright how close you are,

how near
your 
face is

to mine.

too near doesn't exist anymore and when you snored, i couldn't help
but


smile

twice

and try so hard not to cry.

because if things were different,
if no one needed everything, if i were brave if

smiles were really enough

if i could break my own heart,
things would be different.

without a doubt, darling.


if we had fallen asleep, i never would have been allowed out of my

room again.

it may have been worth it. especially now that you don't talk anymore.

you laugh but you don't ask, you smile but you can't care.


for the next ten minutes, i'll sit here and pretend i haven't regretted
it since the moment it

didn't

happen.

for the next ten lifetimes i'll pretend the last five years 

didn't

happen. that i didn't want to fall asleep on top of your shoulder and
that if i didn't believe in you you wouldn't be real.

for the next ten minutes i'll dream until i wake up again and


none of this was ever real.

I rarely don't remind people of someone. I melt and meld and mold myself into someone they knew when they were eight, or their first girlfriend, or their nanny, or their old English teacher, or a waitress they had on their first date with their dead husband, or a person they met just yesterday, or a woman in a movie. 

It blows my mind.



I need to talk.

I need to smile.

I need to listen, to be taught, to be told.

I need to laugh.

I need to know.

I need to learn.

I need to blow bubbles.

I need sunshine.

I need snow.

I need milkshakes.

I need coffee mugs.

I need choices.

I need music.

I need love.

I need hot pink, dark grey water bottles.

I need to be able to misspell.

I need to be equal.

I need to get a little high on life sometimes.

I need to freeze. 

I need pictures.

I need to sing.

I need to act.

I need to meet new people, fall in love with friendships, play.

I need wrong sunrises.

I need right sunsets.

I need graveyards.

I need classrooms.

I need to fight.

I need to run.

I need to walk.

I need to memorize.

I need to grin.

I need bouncy balls.

I need beaches. Oceans. Seashells.

I need bright lights, big cities.

I need not to hate.

I need traffic jams. 

I need freedom.

I need time to move faster. To slow down. To pause. To stop.

I need to live.

I need to call. 

I need to dance. Poorly.

I need to be able to rip off my shirt without a moment's notice.

I need opportunity.

I need the element of surprise.

I need new.

I need old.

I need people.

I need to be able to please everyone I can, and forget everyone I can't.

I need missimg you.

I need camp.

I need books.

I need beds.

I need woods.

I need windows.

I need Shakespeare.

I need life.

Sometimes I smile at strangers. Sometimes I drink too much. Sometimes I fall in love too easy. Sometimes I fall through windows. Sometimes I like being rescued. Sometimes I think I should keep a diary. Sometimes I cry because the simplest things make me happy. Sometimes I lose underwear. Sometimes I obsess. Sometimes I wish I were a gay man. Sometimes I wish I weren't backstage. Sometimes I feel like I could never be happy like I am right now ever again. Sometimes it hurts, but sometimes I'm ok with that. Sometimes someone can say two sentences and kill me, and not even realize it. Sometimes I wish I could relive seven moments forever. Sometimes silence makes me happy. Sometimes being surprised makes me break down. Sometimes I wait for hours for one perfect moment. When it comes, life feels worthwhile. Sometimes I can't believe how lucky I am. Sometimes I miss people so bad that it physically pains me. Sometimes I create excuses solely to visit. Sometimes I call myself to see how I'm doing. Sometimes I worry this is all a dream. Sometimes I surprise myself at how mellow I can be. Sometimes I laugh too hard at nothing. Sometimes it's endearing. Sometimes I wish I were one year older. Sometimes the idea of one more year of high school is overpowering. Sometimes I think about finishing in December. Sometimes I lie. Sometimes I bite my fingernails when I'm worried. Sometimes I don't notice till someone points it out. Sometimes I get lost. Sometimes I gotta move. Sometimes I gotta draw something. Sometimes I gotta beat this need to stay still. Sometimes I worry that one of you will die. Sometimes I worry that that would break my heart. I want to play laser tag.

"here's looking at you kid."

"they call me madame tibbs!"

"i know. why don't you come down sometime and see me? i'm still big, it's the movies that got small."

"i want to be alone. after all, tomorrow is another day."

"what we have here, is a failure to communicate."

"say it again, sam"

"you can't handle the truth... you know that there's no place like home."

"go ahead. make my day. tell me what you've told every other woman you've ever knwon."

"you don't understand. i coulda had class. i coulda been a contender. i could've been someone, instead of a bum. which is what i am."

"we'll always have paris..."

"frankly, my dear, i don't give a damn."

"listen to me, mister. you're my knight in shining armor. don't you forget it. you're going to get back on that horse, and i'm going to be right behind you, holding on tight, and away we're gonna go, go, go!" 

"mrs. robinson, you're trying to seduce me, aren't you?"

"well, darling, nobody's perfect."

"... i already know i had you at hello."

"oh, jerry, let's not ask for the moon. we have the stars."

"carpe diem. seize the day, my dear. make your life extraordinary."

"oh, but sugar, listen to the nightengale. divas of the night. what music they make."

"you always have depended on the kindness of strangers, darling."

"but we know it wasn't the ariplanes. it wasn't the birds. 'twas beauty killed the beast."

"of all the gin joints in all of the world, you had to be the girl to walk into mine."
It makes me angry whenever I think about how unreal it is.

Sometimes I arbitrarily fall in love with literary characters.

Sometimes I imagine loving Hamlet.

Sometimes I feel like the world has bigger problems than mine, so I blink twice and let them fly away.

Sometimes I rewrite Shakespeare in my head.

Sometimes I write the soundtracks for movies of books I've read.

Sometimes I read a novel that changes my outlook on everything.

Sometimes I smile at myself when no one's looking.

Sometimes I talk to strangers because my mind has grown mundane.

Sometimes I like to know.

Sometimes I like surprises.

Sometimes I wish I were Ingrid Bergman. Lauren Bacall. Isadora Duncan.

Sometimes I lie on my floor and watch the lazy ceiling fan.

Sometimes I picture being insane. 

Sometimes I feel my wrists start to prickle whenever anyone mentions Sylvia Plath.

Sometimes I worry about people.

Sometimes I wish I were five years older.

Sometimes I wish I could be seventeen in every deacde from the 20s on.

Sometimes I pretend I'm Zelda Sayre.

Sometimes I wish I could know Ernest Hemmingway. Tom Stoppard. Theron Raines. Thorton Wilder. Gertrude Stein. Pablo Picasso. Charlie Chaplain. F. Scott Fitzgerald. God, F. Scott Fitzgerald.

Sometimes I want to be someone's Daisy.

Sometimes I hate Daisy for killing Gatsby. 

Sometimes I find myself falling in love with Gatsby. 

Sometimes, when I see a long, dark green car, I cry.


"There are no second acts in American lives."

My parents have apparently decided the next five years of my life for me. They tell me I'm going to UC and I'm living in the two family that we own that is literally five houses away from the house I grew up in. And less that a half a mile away from my house now. With no chance of parole. And if I think that if I didn't make it into UC, I could go somewhere else, I'm wrong. My second choice (according to them) is NKU. And then Xavier. It may sound corny, but I don't think I've ever been more heartbroken and depressed. I had such huge plans. New York and Bard and NYU, Chicago and DePaul, Boston, even Antioch. Instead I don't even get a chance at living my own life, because I'd apparently fail miserably at it. They treat it like it's a joke. They never go to any college information meetings, they find it a hassle to come in and have the MANDATORY Junior year conference, so much so that they even called the school to see if there was any way they could cancel it. No one believes that my parents won't allow me to go on college visits. That it isn't important enough to bother with, in their minds. That it has no impression on how the college really is. My father believes that all college is is a communist scheme to seperate you from your money. "The Communist Manifesto" by Michael Flanders. I'm not allowed to make my own choices. They treat it like I'm a burden, and so is sending me to college. It's condescension in the worst form. They act like they're being perfectly rational about it. Like I'm the insane one for assuming that my life would me something like my own after I graduated high school. There used to be a countdown of how many days I had left till graduation. I took it down. It's barely worth dreaming about nothing. They call me ungrateful.

I still hate standardzed tests. 205 in the 97th percentile? It damn well better be high enough. I will freak OUT if Mrs. Gellar comes to talk to me about "The Benefits of 'Lunch Bunch'".

Get your own Twelve Days:

Come and see Oklahoma this weekend [Nov 16th, 17th and 18th at 7:30 PM]


If only to beat up the cast because they made me cry.




That'd be pretty amazing.








Plus it's my birthday Saturday (Rocky Horror, anyone?).




Plus, TJ's making {[his mom make]} me a cake. And that's the closest TJ gets to really really nice.



And I love you.


And and and.... I miss Michael Woodson lots and lots and lots, and I love him dearly. And I miss Jasmine too, because she's amazing. And yeah, I miss Claire Jones lots aussi, parce-qui SHE IS SICK AS A DOG. AND NOT AT SCHOOL. MEANING I HAVEN'T SEEN HER SINCE THURSDAY. But I think she's still alive. According to her xanga anyway...

I miss so many people. So so much that it physically hurts. And my heart may explode if I don't get to see them very very soon. I feel like I don't spend nearly enough time surrounded by people. Either I know too many people or there aren't enough minutes in a year. I tend to favor the second. *I know I dream a lot But I'd do it full-time If the position was open*

Sometimes all I want to do is run away and never look back on anyone who knows me now. Sometimes I want to build a stage in my backyard and act all day. Sometimes I want to tell everyone I know exactly what I think about them. Sometimes I think all my problems will be solved as soon as graduation comes. Sometimes I smile at the neighbors when they're outside on their cellphones. Most of the time they just scowl back. But it's nice when they smile at me too. Sometimes I worry I'm not good enough at any one thing to excell in it and make it a career. Sometimes I think I'm only mediocre. Sometimes I think it's not worth it to get angry, because all I ever do is grin and smile again as soon as someone makes me laugh. Sometimes I wish my mirror really did lead to Wonderland, like I used to say it did in grade school. Sometimes I'm jealous of people older than me. Sometimes I like to lay out on the grass at two in the morning in the backyard, with a blanket and the New York Times Style section. Sometimes I call adults by their first names and feel completely awkward doing so, so I don't call them anything. Sometimes obvious things slip past me. Sometimes I pretend that I'm on my own when I'm making dinner. Sometimes I sing too loud in the shower, and my mom laughs at me when I get out. Sometimes I dream about car crashes, but I'm never driving. Sometimes, at night, I hear someone stirring tea in my kitchen. I'm too afraid to go see what it is most times. Sometimes I smile at strangers, and hold the door open for them. My family sttributes this to my Montessori upbringing. I just think I'm a good person. But sometimes I don't.

It seems like whenever I'm feeling down or low or bored to death by everything, all I have to do is go shopping with Ken and leave Michael a ridiculously longwinded, beautiful comment about nothing and everything and be around Nick for three and a half seconds talking about Dr Ruth and football games and Grecian urns before, suddenly, everything seems ok again. *Do what you love. Fuck everything else.*

I feel like an 
old man who shouts out allelujias to his Chiropractor
Keep holy the day of the Doctor's Visit,
No sex, no work, keep kosher.

Argh.


I feel loopy.

And ready to take on the <u>wooooorld</u>.

The man in the moon looked sideways tonight. And anguished. His halfopen mouth and shocked expression played her heartstrings like a Stradivarius violin and invoked pity. No woman in the moon lived there with him. He only had the hard hot fickle sun he chased and never caught. But then, she thought, It doesn't have to be anguish. The moon's wide smile and feminine charm evoked the spirit of the chased, not the chastened.

*le sigh*

I dreamt that I met the Backstreet Boys, and was best friends with Nick Carter.
And then they all signed my piece of paper with these longwinded year-book-y responses.

And Tyler starred in a movie with Aaron Carter and all the little brothers of the Backstreet Boys.

And then we ran into Jeremy and Giles and Matt and Nick Rose and Guthrie, and they signed my piece of paper too, and drew pictures.

And then I spent the night at Claire's house and we went on Instant Pageant Star, and then walked in on her parents in the kitchen while Claire was trying to make a snow cake.

But on the way to Claire's house, immigration came and tried to deport our luggage and a baby, but I rescued my summer homework and said baby by bribing them with my shoes.

And then Emily, Claire and I did this intense, random scavenger hunt where Nick Carter met up with us again and we had to take pictures of us eating a ballpark hotdog and performing "All's Well that Ends Well" with fish (which is when Jeremy came in and started directing us around- very seriously, might I add) and showering fully clothed.

And then Nick (my Nick) came over and we ran off with a tent to Boston, and camped in the middle of a big park.




It made me smile in my sleep.

Dear world--

I love you.

I love people. In any way, shape or form, regardless of whether we get along or we mesh, I could never live un-surrounded. Everyone talks about how nice it is to hide away on your own for a while but god, life in a New Jersey suburb with no neighbors on either side for ten miles sounds like absolute hell. I love always having someone new to run into and knock over and start a coversation with. No one talks anymore. They're curt and they're crass and they're harsh and they're cruel, but no one ever wants to be curteous. No one will stand in line without complaining to everyone else in the line. No one will wait for food. No one enjoys sitting in traffic, no one takes it as an opprotunity to shout out the lyrics to all the songs that come on the radio and dance and look like a moron in front of someone you'll never see again because you can and because you want to. Life is so much nicer and so much shorter and so much fuller and so much more amazing than people give it credit for. It makes me angry when someone says they hate it. Smile. Fall in love. Smell a tulip. Plant a tree in a pot and gift it to your neighbor. Play in a sprinkler when you're thirty-two. Go on road trips. Take advantage of every opportunity you get to laugh. To cry. To sing. Learn an entire Tom Stoppard play by heart. Watch movies, no matter how awful they are. Laugh at corny jokes. Age gracefully. Never mow your lawn- let it turn into a jungle. Ignore what bothers you. Be photogenic. Be kind. Be friendly. Be loveable. Be original. Be.

So yea, I love Jasmine. And Ken, and Band Camp, and driving.


And being independent <3

Smile.

Right now.

Cuz I love you.

*You can't stop an avalanche as it races down the hill You can try to stop the seasons, girl, but you know you never will And you can try to stop my dancing feet, but I just cannot stand still!* So today... *'Cause the world keeps spinnin' round and round And my heart's keepin' time to the speed of the sound I was lost 'til I heard the drums, then I found my way* I left my house at 9:15 this morning with Nick for work... *'Cause you can't stop the beat* And at work... *Ever since the whole world began A woman found out if she shook it, she could shake up a man And so I'm gonna shake and shimmy it with all of my might today* The plumber came without Cynthia warning me... *'Cause you can't stop the motion of the ocean or the sun in the sky You can wonder, if you wanna, but I never ask why And you can try to hold me down, but I'll spit in your eye and say That You Can't Stop the Beat!* And finally "fixed" the water filter. *You can't stop the river as it rushes to the sea You can try to stop the hands of time, but you know it just won't be! And if they try to stop us, Seaweed, I've got the N double A C P* And then , after solving a billion issues about the "B word" and delivering papers... *Cause the world keeps spinnin round and round And my heart's keepin time to the speed of sound I was lost 'til I heard the drums, then I found my way Cause you cant stop the beat!* I come downstairs... *You can't stop my happiness, cause I like the way I am And you just can't stop my knife and fork when I see a Christmas Ham! And if you don't like the way I look, well, I just dont give a damn!* To Nick holding the top part of the dishwasher and whimpering because it had just BROKEN off in his hands. So guess who spent TWO AND A HALF HOURS fixing the motherfreaking dishwasher with a POT as a hammer and Nick holding the stupid mesh thing while I JAMMED the prongy things back on. But since I'm a complete BEAST, I fixed it. And when I told Cynthia, she goes "Oh, yeah, that happens all the time, we normally just ignore it and jam the whole thing back in, Hu." Oh man. I hate her. And I still haven't been paid for last Thursday. Grr.
